			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Wow,i've had this belt for as long as i can remember. This quest can be done at<BR>
any level but i wouldn't recomend it to any druid below lvl 19 simply for gating <BR>
purposes. It starts in Rivervale but you can skip that part..you need to go to <BR>
West Karana and get &quot;hay&quot; off the millers farm, it spawns on the floor and sometimes <BR>
the millers sell it.  Then you have to head to the temple of life in Qyenos (the temple<BR>
with the UFO) speak to one of the guys on the grounds out there (I forget his name) and<BR>
ask him about the blessed oil.  He will then give you the oil (no drop/lore).  Now that <BR>
you have the hay and the oil you need to head to <BR>
Ferrott and find an NPC lizardman named Rorar (sp?), he spawns just across the river from<BR>
the Temple of Cazic Thule. Hail him and ask him to bless you hay. You need to give him <BR>
95gps and the hay and in return you get cursed hay. Now you take the Cursed hay and Blessed<BR>
Oil back to Rivervale, combine them in a forge and you'll get back shakey stuffing (looks like a <BR>
backpack) Give that to Reebo i think and you should get your Belt of the River.<BR>
<BR>
*note* I've done this quest 4 times back in the day and NEVER got a<BR>
Wee Harvester..just another belt (which is lore)<BR>
<BR>
Good Luck, I did this quest a while ago so if any of the inforation is slightly off,<BR>
I'm sorry, but at least you got the general idea now
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
